# Pendulum with non-linear equation

$$mL^2\ddot{\theta} + b \dot{\theta} + mgL sin(\theta) = \Gamma $${#eq:eq1}

Where b is drag, Î“ is external force applied to pendulum.

We make some substitutions given by @eq:eq2 to make @eq:eq1 dimentionless.

$$\alpha = \frac{b}{Lm\sqrt{gL}},\quad I = \frac{\Gamma}{mgL}, \quad
t=t'/\sqrt{g/L}$$ {#eq:eq2}



## Final system

$$\ddot{\theta} + sin(\theta) + \alpha\dot{\theta} = I$$ {#eq:eq3}

$$ \begin{gathered}
\dot{\theta} = \omega \\
\dot{\omega} = I - sin(\theta) - \alpha \omega
\end{gathered}
$$ {#eq:system}

